multiplier.description: Change the value of this token to modify every token in the scales.

base.description: Tokens used as the default or "mid-point" in your scale will have this value without any changes. So when you adjust only the multiplier token, this is not affected.

default.description:
This token matches a design property in Figma that does not have a direct CSS equivellent. In this system it will always be a zero value token, and designers should use a line break to create paragraph spacing which better matches how

are written in code.
There is no proper way to define a responsive value for this property so it will remain a zero property value in this system.

default.description: Default typography style for the largest paragraph text (p1).

interactive.description: Style for large interactive text elements (e.g., large call-to-action links) needing an underline affordance. Inherits p1 metrics.

strong.description: Emphasized (typically bolder) typography style for level 5 headings (h5).

strong.description: Emphasized (typically bolder) typography style for level 3 headings (h3).

subtle.description: Subtle (typically lighter/regular weight) typography style for level 3 headings (h3).

strong.description: Emphasized (typically bolder) typography style for level 2 headings (h2).

subtle.description: Subtle (typically lighter/regular weight) typography style for level 2 headings (h2).

subtle.description: Subtle (typically lighter/regular weight) typography style for level 1 headings (h1).

strong.description: Bolder style for d3 display headings, increasing visual weight for impactful statements.

subtle.description: Lighter/regular weight style for d3 display headings, offering a less heavy option for large statements.

default.description: Default style for level 2 display headings (d2), used for very large typographic statements in marketing or hero sections.

strong.description: Bolder style for d2 display headings, maximizing visual weight for key statements.

subtle.description: Lighter/regular weight style for d2 display headings, providing a lighter alternative for major typographic moments.

default.description: Default style for the largest display headings (d1), used for primary, highly impactful typographic statements, typically in hero sections (largest display size).

strong.description: Bolder style for d1 display headings, for maximum visual impact and weight.

subtle.description: Lighter/regular weight style for d1 display headings, offering a refined option for the largest typographic statements.

default.description: Font metrics (size, default weight, line height, etc.) for small interactive UI elements like small labels, controls, or compact button text. Color and specific decoration applied separately.

strong.description: Font metrics (size, default weight, line height, etc.) for small interactive UI elements like small labels, controls, or compact button text. Color and specific decoration applied separately.

default.description: Font metrics for standard-sized interactive UI elements (e.g., default button text, standard control labels). Color and specific decoration applied separately.

strong.description: Font metrics for standard-sized interactive UI elements (e.g., default button text, standard control labels). Color and specific decoration applied separately.

default.description: Font metrics for large interactive UI elements (e.g., large button text). Color and specific decoration applied separately.

strong.description: Font metrics for large interactive UI elements (e.g., large button text). Color and specific decoration applied separately.

p4.description: Part of typography. Rare, use for extra-small, non-essential text like legal disclaimers or tiny metadata where space is highly constrained. Non-readable

p3.description: Part of typography. Use for small supporting text: captions, metadata, helper text below inputs, small labels.

p2.description: Part of typography. The standard workhorse size for body content, descriptions, and primary UI text.

p1.description: Part of typography. Use for lead paragraphs, block quotes, or other larger body text needing strong.

h6.description: Part of typography. The smallest heading level, for fine-grained sectioning within components or detailed content.

h5.description: Part of typography. For sub-sections within components like cards, or for grouping related controls.

h4.description: Part of typography. For distinct sections within a page region or complex component; provides clear visual grouping.

h3.description: Part of typography. For major content sections or titles of significant UI modules.

h2.description: Part of typography. For primary page sections or secondary page titles, establishing major divisions.

h1.description: Part of typography. Primarily reserved for the main title of a page or view.

d3.description: Part of typography. The smallest display size, for impactful but secondary headlines in marketing or feature areas.

d2.description: Part of typography. A large display size for key marketing headlines or significant feature titles.

d1.description: Part of typopgraphy. The largest display size, reserved for primary hero messaging or major branding moments.

tight.description: Part of typography. Use for large headings (especially display sizes) to reduce excess space between lines and improve visual cohesion.

default.description: Part of typography. Optimal line height for readability of standard body text blocks.

relaxed.description: Part of typography. Use for a more open, airy feel in body text, improving readability for some users or contexts.

tight.description: Part of typography. Use for large headings (especially display sizes) to reduce excess space between lines and improve visual cohesion.

relaxed.description: Part of typography. Use when extra space is desired around headings for visual separation or style.

default.description: Part of typography. Standard letter spacing for optimal readability in body text (usually 0). em units

tighter.description: Part of typography. Apply to very large display headings (d1, d2) to optically tighten spacing for visual appeal. em units.

tight.description: Part of typography. Apply to large headings (h1, h2, d3) for improved visual density and impact.. em units

default.description: Part of typography. Standard (often slightly negative) spacing for most headings (h3-h6) to enhance cohesion. em units

relaxed.description: Part of typography. Use for headings needing an open, airy feel, or potentially for all-caps headings (usually 0 or slightly positive). em units

s.description: Defines the upper boundary (max-width) for the smallest screen size layout (e.g., mobile portrait).

m.description: Defines the upper boundary for medium screen layouts (e.g., tablet portrait/landscape).

l.description: Defines the upper boundary for standard desktop screen layouts.

xl.description: Defines the upper boundary for large desktop screen layouts.

s.description: Specifies the number of grid columns available in the small breakpoint layout.

m.description: Specifies the number of grid columns available in the medium breakpoint layout.

l.description: Specifies the number of grid columns available in the large (and above) breakpoint layout.

s.description: Size for small, often inline or incidental icons.

m.description: Standard icon size used alongside regular text or in controls.

ml.description: Size for larger, more prominent icons, perhaps in illustrations or section headers.

xl.description: Size for extra-large icons used for significant visual impact or empty states OR icon backgrounds/bounds

xs.description: Height/width for extra-small, dense controls like compact buttons or icon-only buttons.

l.description: Height/width for large, prominent controls like primary call-to-action buttons.

xl.description: Height/width for extra-large controls used in high-strong situations or specific layouts.

none.description: Use for full-bleed layouts where content extends to the viewport edge.

scale.description: I added a scale here to be able to change the roundness of all border-radiuses simultaneously. That can be a very nice mechanism for several other tokens.

s.description: Subtle rounding for containers, providing a slightly softer look.

m.description: Standard rounding for containers like cards and modals.

default.description: The core brand color used as the base for primary actions and highlights.

hover.description: Represents the hover state color for primary brand elements. The actual color value MUST be defined/overridden in the specific product theme set, typically a slightly lighter variant of the primary default color.

pressed.description: Represents the pressed/active state color for primary brand elements. The actual color value MUST be defined/overridden in the specific product theme set. Usually darker variant of default

disabled.description: The effective color/appearance for disabled primary brand elements (often derived via opacity).

default.description: The core brand color used as the base for secondary actions and elements.

hover.description: The brand color variant used for hover states on secondary elements.

pressed.description: The brand color variant used for pressed states on secondary elements.

disabled.description: The effective color/appearance for disabled secondary brand elements (often derived via opacity).

default.description: The primary background color for the overall page or main content areas (typically white in light mode).

subtle.description: A slightly off-default background color used for subtle differentiation, like card backgrounds, sidebars, or grouped sections (typically light gray in light mode).

subtlest.description: A slightly off-default background color used for subtle differentiation, like card backgrounds, sidebars, or grouped sections (typically light gray in light mode).

primary.description: Primary text color for high contrast readability. Override for dark themes.

secondary.description: Secondary text color for less emphasis (e.g., descriptions, metadata).

disabled.description: Text color for disabled elements.

onBrand.description: Default text color on primary brand backgrounds. Ensure WCAG contrast is met based on the specific brand color used.

onColor.description: Default text color on other colored backgrounds (e.g., feedback alerts). Ensure WCAG contrast.

default.description: Default link text color. Override in product sets if links should use a different color.

hover.description: Hover state for link text. Override if needed.

pressed.description: Pressed state for link text. Inherits primary brand hover color by default. Override if needed.

visited.description: Color for text links that have been previously visited by the user.

disabled.description: Disabled background for error interactive elements. Uses transparency 40%.

multiplier.description: Change the value of this token to modify every token in the scales.

base.description: Tokens used as the default or "mid-point" in your scale will have this value without any changes. So when you adjust only the multiplier token, this is not affected.
